    "summary": "I am educational advisor for online learning at the University of Groningen, Netherlands. \nI hold an MSc in e-learning, University of Edinburgh, UK and Master in Pedagogics and Creative Learning, Democritus University of Thrace, Greece and a PhD in elearning, Open University of Catalonia, Spain.\n\nI am particularly interested in online course design, both as a researcher and as a practitioner. So far, I have designed and developed online courses for the MA in DTLT as well as several online and blended-learning short professional development courses addressed to adults, teachers, and teacher educators.\n\nIn collaboration with a few fellow educators I started in 2012 an initiative called ICT4ALL with the triple aim to support teachers in developing digital competences for lifelong learning, help them strengthen their knowledge of how to use digital technologies in their daily teaching practice, and promote openness of educational practices. Towards this goal we developed an online survey to gather teachers\u2019 opinions and preferences as regards digital tools, we planned and run several blended learning courses, we developed and maintain an online platform on Moodle to host our courses, and we are supporting a growing community of teachers who publish their activities and digital artifacts on a collaborative blog. In 2016 the ICT4ALL initiative was accredited as one of the best practices in Open Education by the Open Education Europa.\nI am a MirandaNet fellow and regular reviewer in academic journals and conferences. For several years I was guiding and mentoring teachers during their introduction in the eTwinning and Teachers4Europe programmes. I am also supervising postgraduate students\u2019 dissertations at the MA in DTLT.",
