                    "company": "Universitat Oberta de Catalunya",
                    "description": "In 2017 I received a scholarship to study towards a PhD degree in e-learning at the Open University of Catalonia. \nIn the first year of my doctorate studies, I mainly reviewed the literature on how students learn online and how technology could support their efforts. Under the directions of my supervisor, I submitted a proposal for the construction of a new Virtual Learning Environment that would facilitate students\u2019 learning and inquiry activities. Although my proposal received very positive feedback both from my supervisor and the programming team, unfortunately at that time the university could not allocate the required resources for its construction. \nAfter discussing with my supervisor on ways to continue, we agreed to conduct research on the teacher-inquirer identity in face-to-face and online environments. Therefore, after reviewing the relevant literature I constructed two self-report questionnaires on components related to the development of the teacher-inquirer identity and I sent these questionnaires to the respective populations. \nI presented preliminary results of my thesis at three conferences (ICERI 2019, EDEN 2020, and EARLI SIG14) and I also wrote a book chapter in collaboration with my supervisor. My thesis is titled: 'Teacher-inquirer identity in light of educational innovation and during online master thesis: Examination of the inquiry skills and other related components' and I will defend it this winter.",
                    "title": "PHD Researcher",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
